Former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani-Kayode, has reacted to the court ruling sentencing former Governor of Abia State, Orji Uzor Kalu to twelve years in prison. DAILY POST had reported that a Federal High Court in Lagos on Thursday found Kalu, guilty of 39 counts of N7.2 billion fraud and money laundering. Kalu was charged alongside Jones Udeogo, the state Commissioner for Finance during his tenure as the governor. Ruling, Justice Mohammed Idris sentenced him to 12 years in prison. The court also ordered that the Slok Nig. Ltd be shut down and its assets forfeited to the Federal Government. Reacting, Fani-Kayode on Twitter revealed that all persons convicted of corruption since Buhari came to power are Christians. He wrote, ”Every former Governor and key former public office holder that has been convicted of corruption since Buhari came to power from Jolly Nyame to Joshua Dariye to Bala Ngilari to Orji Kalu are Christians. ”Make of it what you will but that is a fact. Is it only Christians that steal?” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.